Notice: You must compile the package with gcc 3.0 or higher. Other
compilers may not work.

Three steps to install:
 1. run "./configure" script to config various options. You can try:
    ./configure   build with default settings (recommended)
  or
    ./configure --enable-static will build a static linked binaries
  or
    ./configure --help will bring you more options

 2. type "make" to build the software

 3. type "make install" to install the software

